text.paragraph:
The usefulness of agents of this class (see 
                        CLINICAL PHARMACOLOGY
                     ) should be measured against possible risk factors inherent in their use such as those described below. Diethylpropion hydrochloride is indicated for use as monotherapy only.

Because diethylpropion hydrochloride is a monoamine, hypertension may result when this agent is used with monoamine oxidase (MAO) inhibitors (see 
                              CONTRAINDICATIONS
                           ).
